[h2 id=EffortInTasing 
	"Effort In TASing
	$LF
]h2
[div class=p 
	"I have been working on the C64 version and wondered if I had learned anything that could be used on the Colecovision version. So, I started TASing the coleco game, while avoiding the inputs from 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/MESHUGGAH 
		"MESHUGGAH
	]a
	"'s 
	(__wikiLink|href=/5808S|implicitdisplaytext=5808S)
	"...as I didn't want any influence to take away from my understanding thus far. Well, it turned out 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/MESHUGGAH 
		"MESHUGGAH
	]a
	"'s inputs were rock solid! The only thing that showed up was a difference found when jumping the top of the volcano, by use of the bird. Something in the cut scene causes a timing issue (Frame Rule maybe?) that would soon be resolved by the end of Stage 6. Thereafter, each stage was 2 frames faster and that is how it ended...with a 2 frame cut. All I had to do, was hold that ground until the game was finished. 
	$LF
]div
